## 1. Objects

- `base_operand(t) = w(t) = 1 - x_term(t)`. Per fixture:
  - pure_algebraic: `t = x`, `x_term = x`  => `w = 1 - t`,    `w' = -1`,           `w'' = 0`.
  - Schwarzschild:  `t = r`, `x_term = 2/r` => `w = 1 - 2/t`,  `w' = 2/t^2`,        `w'' = -4/t^3`.
  - SR:             `t = beta`, `x_term = b^2` => `w = 1 - t^2`, `w' = -2t`,         `w'' = -2`.
- natural function `y = sqrt(w)` (the curve the geometry table reads).
- fingerprint `F(t) = log2|w| = (1/ln2) ln w`  (w > 0 on all relevant domains).

